<c74object name='dk.rungler~' category='' module='dataknot'>
    <digest>Rungler-inspired oscillator
</digest>
    <description>The <o>dk.rungler~</o> object is a digital recreation of the Rob Hordijk Rungler. The rungler is basically a CMOS shift register clocked by one oscillator and receiving its data input from the other oscillator. To describe the rungler waveform in similar terms as like a sine wave or pulse wave. Rob calls it a &quot;stepped havoc wave&quot;.
</description>
    <discussion>Based on the Rob Hordijk Rungler. For more information visit <a href="https://sdiy.info/wiki/Rob_Hordijk_Rungler">https://sdiy.info/wiki/Rob_Hordijk_Rungler</a>
</discussion>

	<metadatalist>
		<metadata name='author'>Rodrigo Constanzo, FluCoMa Project</metadata>
		<metadata name='tag'>Machine Learning</metadata>
		<metadata name='tag'>Audio Analysis</metadata>
		<metadata name='tag'>Onset Detection</metadata>
		<metadata name='tag'>Corpus Playback</metadata>
	</metadatalist>

